        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Fix suppressed heartbeat commitment delivery",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #91948.\n\n- Treat durable `suppressed` heartbeat sends as non-visible delivery, not successful commitment delivery.\n- Keep due commitments pending and avoid writing heartbeat dedupe state when the durable send is suppressed.\n- Emit a skipped heartbeat event with the durable suppression reason, then allow a later visible heartbeat to retry and mark the commitment sent.\n- Add a regression test covering a suppressed `No channel reply.` heartbeat followed by a visible retry.\n\n## Root Cause\n\n`runHeartbeatOnce` called `sendDurableMessageBatch`, threw only for failed/partial failed statuses, and then treated every other result as delivered. That meant a `suppressed` durable result from outbound planning could mark inferred commitments `sent`, write `lastHeartbeatText`/`lastHeartbeatSentAt`, and emit a `sent` heartbeat event even though no channel message was visible.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local` - clean; no accepted/actionable findings reported; overall patch correct `(0.86)`.\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/infra/heartbeat-runner.commitments.test.ts -- --reporter=verbose` - 10 tests passed after rebase.\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/channels/message/send.test.ts src/channels/turn/durable-delivery.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/route-reply.test.ts -- --reporter=verbose` - 54 tests passed.\n- Regression repro: with only the runtime fix temporarily reverted, the new focused test failed on current behavior with `expected 'sent' to deeply equal 'pending'`; after restoring the fix, the focused test passed.\n- Live AWS Crabbox proof, run `run_6ac6aacdd5f2`: first suppressed Telegram heartbeat left the commitment `pending`, kept `sentAtMs` unset, did not write heartbeat dedupe state, and emitted `skipped` with `reason: no_visible_payload`; the next visible heartbeat sent exactly one Telegram message and marked the commitment `sent`.\n",
        "branch": "fix/91948-heartbeat-suppressed-commitments",
